        end_time_formatted: "2025-12-19 23:59",
        detail: "Step into an enchanting world with Carolina Ballet Theatre Greenville’s professional Ballet Company as they present \"The Nutcracker: Once Upon a Time in Greenville,\" a delightful twist on a beloved classic. \nOn a magical Christmas Eve, excitement ﬁlls the air as Clara and her brother, Fritz, eagerly await the evening\'s festivities. Friends and family arrive by train, reveling in the charm of Greenville’s picturesque Main Street, ready to join the celebration. The mysterious Herr Drosselmeyer, Clara\'s enigmatic godfather, makes a grand entrance, delighting everyone with gifts, including a unique nutcracker that holds a special place in Clara’s heart. \nAs the evening unfolds with laughter and joyful dancing, a playful mishap propels Herr Drosselmeyer into a whimsical adventure, guided by a twinkling star and glimpses of Clara’s remarkable future. Audiences will be captivated by the journey that features epic battles, magical realms of dancing sweets, and a stunning debutante ball. The story culminates in the breathtaking moment when Clara, now a beautiful bride, steps into her new life. \nThis charming production, infused with the spirit of Greenville, promises to leave spectators spellbound. Witness the courageous transformation of the Nutcracker from a wooden soldier to a valiant prince, and share in the heartwarming tale of Clara\'s blossoming love. Prepare to uncover the magic of Christmas Eve in this unforgettable celebration that weaves together dreams, adventure, and the joy of the season!",
        location: "Peace Center SW corner of Broad St. and Main St. Downtown Greenville, South Carolina",
